author: JUSTIN TASCH
title: TV newsman mistakenly reports Michigan win vs Michigan State
text:
TV newsman mistakenly reports Michigan win vs Michigan State New York Daily News 12 hrs ago JUSTIN TASCH Â© Provided by New York Daily News A fumble by Michigan punter Blake O'Neill allows Michigan State to pull off the miraculous victory. - Tony Ding/AP If you're a Michigan football fan in Grand Rapids and had to get your game news from WZZM Saturday evening, you might've been blissfully ignorant for a few moments.
AdChoices The Wolverines suffered a crushing loss on the final play Saturday to rival Michigan State when their punter fumbled the snap and the Spartans recovered and returned it for a game-winning touchdown as time expired. WZZM reporter Jamal Spencer had no clue.
FOLLOW THE DAILY NEWS SPORTS ON FACEBOOK. "LIKE" US HERE.
"Michigan coming up with a crucial stop, and they were able to run out the clock," Spencer said during his live report . "People are spilling out of Michigan Stadium into the streets of Ann Arbor celebrating as the Paul Bunyan trophy is back in Ann Arbor for the first time since 2012."
A studio anchor corrected Spencer's report as soon as it was over, reporting that Michigan had indeed lost.
CHECK OUT OUR NEW APP: GET THE DAILY NEWS ON ANDROID OR IOS
MOBILE USERS: WATCH THE VIDEO HERE
Spencer tweeted about the erroneous report in response to a Deadspin story late Saturday night.
"Not the first time I've made a mistake in my career and it won't be the last. Gotta take the bad with the good," Spencer wrote.
